commits.commitMessage:
Add support for DW_op_stack_value

GCC will generate variables with location DW_op_stack_value.  Add
code to ignore such variables as this is an indication they
have been optimized out.

Resolves: LE-16550
Change-Id: I1ea5399bd32c135faa02c3afcf6afc28f84921c5
commits.subject: Add support for DW_op_stack_value

commits.commitMessage:
Assign "PAD" symbols to the section surrounding them

If the elfsize analyzer script detects a section of memory and can't
find any symbols associated with it, it creates a "PAD" symbol.
Currently these symbols are not given a section â€“ instead they should be
given the section of the surrounding code or data.

Resolves: LE-16342
Change-Id: I8cab0756366c71825d917f7365f2b65a058bb771
commits.subject: Assign "PAD" symbols to the section surrounding them

commits.commitMessage:
Support overlays in elfsize.py

Support overlays on alt1250-map-pyelftools target.  This required:

 - Adding section as well as address to the symbol key, as two symbols
   in with the same address in different overlays are considered different
   symbols
 - Update RAM usage summary to add the largest overlay to the total
   RAM usage.

Resolves: LE-15636
Change-Id: I733075f89b0b756b1caa36fb91b75a213b314842

commits.commitMessage:
Port pytools-based analysis to HL7800

The pytools-based elfsize.py analysis use on ThreadX products uses
debug info to trace symbols back to their source, so can provide a
more accurate view of memory usage than the previous GNU Toolchain
based solution.  So Port this solution to to HL78 MAP, and use it
as the default size analysis.  Keep the old analysis engine as
alt1250-map-gnu for comparison purposes.

Resolves: LE-15531
Change-Id: If4998ec4f32d6b916e5f53f72f7d562268690527
commits.subject: Port pytools-based analysis to HL7800

commits.commitMessage:
Create wrapper shell script for linkerReport/elfsize.py

This linker script:

 - Copies all .js, .html and .css files needed by the linker report
   into the destination directory.
 - Calls elfsize.py with the correct parameters to put its output
   into this directory.

Typical usage of the new tool is (for rc76):

    linkerReport.sh DESTINATION -d -d mdm9x07-apss-tx -b \
        -i apps_proc/build/ms/M9x06ACDNAAAZA00239.elf

Resolves: LE-14037
Change-Id: Ie65744dc67b44f62fb60f1cb5b4d2cc9e0f2114b
commits.subject: Create wrapper shell script for linkerReport/elfsize.py

commits.commitMessage:
Create elftools toolchain for parsing debug info

Create a "QTIToolchain" in elfsize.py which uses the python elftools
to extract symbol and file location directly from the elf & dwarf.

This change provides better location information on Qualcomm
ThreadX products, so use this new toolchain for those products.

commits.commitMessage:
Add preliminary support for ThreadX image analysis

The APSS images use different section names, and the symbol resolution
falls back to looking up the object file in the linker map if the
source cannot be determined.

Some features were refactored to make adding the new toolchain easier.

Resolves: LE-13695
Change-Id: Iec49461593ed948f9f77d365cb026185bd548792
commits.subject: Add preliminary support for ThreadX image analysis
